snippet: Officials charged the manager of the Tick Tock Diner in Clifton, N.J., with conspiracy to have an undercover trooper posing as a hit man kill his uncle, an owner of the restaurant.
abstract: Authorities report that Georgios Spyropoulos, manager of popular Tick Tock Diner in Clifton, NJ, tried to have his uncle Alexandros Sgourdos, co-owner of the restaurant, killed by a hit man; say Spyropoulos resented control his uncle exerted over diner and felt his uncle was taking unfair share of profits.
lead_paragraph: Officials charged the manager of the Tick Tock Diner in Clifton, N.J., with conspiracy to have an undercover trooper posing as a hit man kill his uncle, an owner of the restaurant.

headline.seo: Manager of Tick Tock Diner Held in Murder Conspiracy
headline.main: Diner Manager Accused of Trying to Have Uncle Killed
headline.print_headline: Diner Manager Accused of Trying to Have Uncle Killed
